Mitigation methods

-reducing the ability of the user to input files from a web application
-limit the ability of the file to be modifies
-use a service that has a special account for the user.









Mitigations Methods of SQL injunction 

-Use of validation to limit users ability to modify files
-The use of servers that have selective user accounts associated with them linked to the web





























Password Mitigation

Use of complex characters
Limit login failures
Multi factor authentication









Mitigation 

Ensure the application has a HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol/Secure)  header has secure cookie attributes
Session cookies are encrypted 
Headers have HTTPOnly cookies attributes(does not allow Java access)
Ensure cookies are min length so it is difficult for brute force

